The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, August 13, 2003 				 Involve Hizb in dialogue: Mehbooba
 MUKHTAR AHMAD 																								Srinagar Aug. 12: Mehbooba Mufti, leader of the ruling Peoples Democratic Party, today said the Hizb-ul Mujahideen must be involved in the dialogue process which alone will result in some honourable solution of the Kashmir issue.																								Addressing a public meeting in the border town of Uri, Mehbooba said: A lasting peace and durable solution of the Kashmir problem cannot be imagined without involving Hizb-ul Mujahideen in the dialogue process.																								Indo-Pakistan talks and involvement of the Hurriyat Conference will not bear fruit until the Hizb is involved to find an honourable solution of the Kashmir imbroglio, she added.																								Mehbooba said opening the Uri-Rawalpindi road would help normalise bilateral relations. Promise to Pundits																								Speaking in Muzaffarabad, Hizb chief Salahuddin promised protection to Pundits and urged them to return to their homes in Kashmir, says a PTI report. 
